The paper discusses the development of a probabilistic programming language for exploring contextuality in a wide range of applications relevant to cognitive science and artificial intelligence. The paper also proposes a hypergraph-based semantics for the language. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of hypergraphs, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IT (information theory), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.SY (systems and control).
